<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="01981ed7-1d06-549b-aea6-ad303388b913" activityNameId="da7ed0db-8a01-4d51-92e3-abfa115117db" parentActivityId="188d1933-0f80-4417-989b-abfa1148b6b0" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">treatment of biowaste, open dump</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the waste being available at the location (gate) of the uncontrolled disposal. Collection and transportation of the waste to the uncontrolled disposal location is not included.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the waste being disposed, in an uncontrolled manner and waste-specific emissions from open dump are released to air via gas and to water via leachate. </includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of 'biowaste' in an open dump. Recommended use of this dataset: uncontrolled disposal of the waste through dumping. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% biomass, 65% water. Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 6.087 MJ/kg; net heating value 4.289 MJ/kg; H2O 650000; O 110270; H 18556; C 141650; S 1307.7; N 3488.9; P 985.61; B 8.9315; Cl 3488.9; Br 5.2333; F 174.44; I 0.047972; Ag na; As 1.7444; Ba na; Cd 0.12037; Co 4.3611; Cr 6.9778; Cu 15.7; Hg 0.061055; Mn 3.7505; Mo 0.34889; Ni 4.7274; Pb 16.188; Sb na; Se 0.4359; Sn 6.9744; V 2.6154; Zn 50.798; Be na; Sc na; Sr na; Ti na; Tl na; W na; Si 34872; Fe 523.33; Ca 19014; Al 8717.9; K 3052.8; Mg 2459.7; Na 1308.3. Share of carbon in initial waste that is biogenic 100%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 27%. 0.0351 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="9a63625a-358b-4c1d-bf95-50ba038a759b">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="7846b897-7c04-4f9f-b607-2b83fcd9a74c">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoW</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents an open dump location with mean annual temperature (MAT) of 16.744 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 1250.8 mm/year, and net infiltration of 790.25 mm/year. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">The leachate percolating through the landfill has an average residence time of 2.21 years.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Reference for climatic parameters: </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">UN data, 2020. Precipitation, Environment Statistics Database, United Nations Statistics Division Available at: http://data.un.org/Data.aspx?q=precipitation&amp;d=ENV&amp;f=variableID%3a6;</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">World Bank, 2022. Surface area (sq.km), World Bank Group Available at: https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/AG.SRF.TOTL.K2;</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Doka G.,2021. A model for composition-specific life cycle inventories of regionalised wastewater fates, Zurich, Switzerland. http://www.doka.ch/publications.htm</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is an inventory for an open, uncontrolled waste dump for municipal solid waste. Ultimate average landfill height is 7 meters. Operation phase duration is 15 years. The total, waste-specific raw landfill gas mass produced in the landfill is 0.004685 kg. The total CH4 mass in the raw landfill gas is 0 kg. Percentage of landfill gas directly emitted is 100w%. A Methane Correction Factor (MCF) for landfill air emissions of 0.7057 is employed. Leachate of the landfill is not treated, but emitted untreated. Based on average waste composition and chosen climate data the end of carbonate phase is estimated to be reached 7789 years after waste deposition.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2010-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
