        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">According to literature, Global municipal solid waste generation is circa 1.3 Billion Mg on a yearly basis. In addition, the organic fraction of it is 46%. The amount of MSW that is driven to dumps on a global scale is circa 9.1%. The aforementioned value is derived as a weighted average value of available data in all countries across the globe. Hence, 54177385299 kg of organic waste is driven to dumps every year. Value refers to 2012. 

Reference: Hoornweg, Daniel; Bhada-Tata, Perinaz. 2012. What a Waste : A Global Review of Solid Waste Management. Urban development series;knowledge papers no. 15. World Bank, Washington, DC.  World Bank. https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/handle/10986/17388 License: CC BY 3.0 IGO.
Zhu, Da; Asnani, P. U.; Zurbrügg, Chris; Anapolsky, Sebastian; Mani, Shyamala. 2008. Improving Municipal Solid Waste Management in India : A Sourcebook for Policy Makers and Practitioners. WBI Development Studies. Washington, DC: World Bank.  World Bank. https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/handle/10986/6916 License: CC BY 3.0 IGO."</productionVolumeComment>
